setWait(WaitObject, ClientController) - Method in class it.polimi.ingsw.client.controller.WaitManager
Takes care of waiting on a specific request / operation, based on the Wait Object passed as a parameter. 1) This function check if the wait has already been used, this means that the data is already available and there is no need to wait, therefore the wait status is reset and the function ends. 2) If the wait has not already been used, this means that the data has not yet arrived and the calling thread must be put on hold with wait.
